<p><alert>II: Equation of a parabola whose axis is parallel to the <em>x</em>-axis</alert>.</p>
<p>A parabola whose axis is parallel to <em><alert>x</alert></em>-axis is called <alert>horizontal parabola</alert>. Such parabola opens either to the right or to the left as shown in Figure 4.15 (a) and (b), respectively.</p>
